---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="ARBE Project – Algorithmic Resource-Based Economy">

  <!-- HERO SECTION -->
  <section style="padding-top: 1rem; padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <div
      style="
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1.2rem;
        max-width: 820px;
      "
    >
      <div
        style="
          display: inline-flex;
          align-items: center;
          gap: 0.6rem;
          padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
          border-radius: 999px;
          border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.35);
          background: rgba(15,23,42,0.7);
          font-size: 0.75rem;
          color: #9ca3af;
        "
      >
        <span
          style="
            width: 8px;
            height: 8px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            background: #22c55e;
            box-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(34,197,94,0.8);
          "
        />
        Public, sovereign & algorithmic monetary architecture
      </div>

      <h1
        style="
          font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 3vw + 1.6rem, 3.6rem);
          line-height: 1.05;
          margin: 0;
          letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        "
      >
        AMN / ARBE<br />
        A new monetary architecture for a resource-aligned future.
      </h1>

      <p
        style="
          font-size: 1.05rem;
          color: #9ca3af;
          max-width: 45rem;
          line-height: 1.65;
        "
      >
        ARBE (Algorithmic Resource-Based Economy) and the AMN sovereign digital currency propose a
        transparent, audited and algorithmically governed monetary framework — where money is no
        longer a tool of debt and control, but a neutral medium to exchange human work and real
        resources.
      </p>

      <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a
          href="/whitepaper"
          style="
            padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
            border-radius: 999px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(56,189,248,0.55);
            background: linear-gradient(
              to right,
              rgba(56,189,248,0.18),
              rgba(129,140,248,0.14)
            );
            color: #e5faff;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 500;
          "
        >
          Read the Whitepaper
        </a>

        <a
          href="#mission"
          style="
            padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
            border-radius: 999px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.5);
            background: rgba(15,23,42,0.9);
            color: #e5e7eb;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
          "
        >
          Learn How It Works
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MISSION -->
  <section id="mission" style="margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2
      style="
        font-size: 1.9rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      "
    >
      Mission & Purpose
    </h2>
    <p style="color: #9ca3af; max-width: 50rem; line-height: 1.65;">
      The current monetary model — based on private credit creation, systemic debt and opaque
      governance — produces structural inequality, inflation cycles, and misallocation of resources.
      ARBE proposes a new paradigm: algorithmic monetary governance, audited resource anchoring
      and deterministic public ledgers.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- PROBLEMS -->
  <section style="margin-bottom: 3.2rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.7rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">The Problem We Address</h2>
    <ul
      style="
        margin-top: 0.8rem;
        padding-left: 1.2rem;
        color: #9ca3af;
        max-width: 48rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
      "
    >
      <li>Extreme inequality & structural poverty</li>
      <li>Perpetual debt cycles & systemic inflation</li>
      <li>Speculation over essential goods (food, water, housing, healthcare)</li>
      <li>Destruction of ecosystems and misaligned incentives</li>
      <li>Private capture of public value</li>
      <li>Recurrent bubbles and financial crises</li>
      <li>Dependence on foreign payment infrastructures like SWIFT</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
  <section style="margin-bottom: 3.2rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.7rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">How ARBE Works</h2>
    <div
      style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));
        gap: 1.6rem;
        margin-top: 1.2rem;
      "
    >
      <div
        style="
          border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.4);
          border-radius: 14px;
          padding: 1rem;
          background: rgba(15,23,42,0.65);
        "
      >
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.1rem;">RTM — Resource Model</h3>
        <p style="color: #9ca3af;">Sensors & audits quantify real productive resources.</p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="
          border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.4);
          border-radius: 14px;
          padding: 1rem;
          background: rgba(15,23,42,0.65);
        "
      >
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.1rem;">SLP — Sovereign Ledger</h3>
        <p style="color: #9ca3af;">Deterministic, public ledger for monetary proofs.</p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="
          border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.4);
          border-radius: 14px;
          padding: 1rem;
          background: rgba(15,23,42,0.65);
        "
      >
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.1rem;">AMN — Algorithmic Currency</h3>
        <p style="color: #9ca3af;">PID-based monetary emission with near-zero structural inflation.</p>
      </div>

      <div
        style="
          border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.4);
          border-radius: 14px;
          padding: 1rem;
          background: rgba(15,23,42,0.65);
        "
      >
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.1rem;">AMA — Autonomous Governance</h3>
        <p style="color: #9ca3af;">Independent, algorithmically constrained monetary authority.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TECHNOLOGY -->
  <section style="margin-bottom: 3.2rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.7rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">Technology Pillars</h2>
    <ul
      style="
        padding-left: 1.2rem;
        color: #9ca3af;
        max-width: 46rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
      "
    >
      <li>Deterministic ledger with cryptographic integrity</li>
      <li>Sensor-driven resource quantification</li>
      <li>Algorithmic monetary policy (PID controller)</li>
      <li>Multi-layer domain separation (resources → monetary)</li>
      <li>Open-source governance models</li>
      <li>Public auditability of all monetary actions</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- GOVERNANCE -->
  <section style="margin-bottom: 3.2rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.7rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em;">Governance: AMA</h2>
    <p style="color:#9ca3af; max-width: 48rem; line-height: 1.6;">
      The Algorithmic Monetary Authority (AMA) is an independent, transparent, algorithmically
      constrained body composed of scientists, engineers, economists, non-profit representatives,
      citizen-elected experts and auditors. Zero political interference. Zero private influence.
      Full transparency.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- CALL TO ACTION -->
  <section style="margin-bottom: 3.2rem;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.7rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">Get Involved</h2>
    <p style="color: #9ca3af; max-width: 48rem; line-height: 1.6;">
      Help us design a fair, transparent and resource-aligned economic system.
      Read the whitepaper, contribute to the documentation, or join the governance discussions.
    </p>

    <div style="display:flex; gap:1rem; margin-top:1rem;">
      <a
        href="/whitepaper"
        style="
          padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
          border-radius: 999px;
          border: 1px solid rgba(56,189,248,0.55);
          background: rgba(56,189,248,0.15);
          color:#e5faff;
        "
      >Read Whitepaper</a>

      <a
        href="/docs"
        style="
          padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
          border-radius: 999px;
          border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.5);
          background: rgba(15,23,42,0.9);
          color:#e5e7eb;
        "
      >Documentation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
